</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Together with 
<taxonomicName authority="Konow, 1899" authorityName="Koch" authorityYear="2006" class="Insecta" family="Argidae" genus="Pampsilota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pampsilota luederitzensis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luederitzensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Pampsilota luederitzensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, also from southwest Africa, 
<taxonomicName authority="Konow, 1899" authorityName="Koch" authorityYear="2006" class="Insecta" family="Argidae" genus="Pampsilota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pampsilota brandbergensis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brandbergensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Pampsilota brandbergensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from other 
<taxonomicName authority="Konow, 1899" authorityName="Konow" authorityYear="1899" class="Insecta" family="Argidae" genus="Pampsilota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pampsilota" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Pampsilota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in its body length of maximally 6.0 mm (other species at least 7.0 mm long). The yellow pronotum and entirely black legs of 
<taxonomicName authority="Konow, 1899" authorityName="Koch" authorityYear="2006" class="Insecta" family="Argidae" genus="Pampsilota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pampsilota brandbergensis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brandbergensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Pampsilota brandbergensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
distinguish it immediately from 
<taxonomicName authority="Konow, 1899" authorityName="Koch" authorityYear="2006" class="Insecta" family="Argidae" genus="Pampsilota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pampsilota luederitzensis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luederitzensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Pampsilota luederitzensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with dark pronotum and largely pale tibia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Variability in colour pattern is scarcely noticeable in the two known specimens, except that tergum 5 as well as sterna 3-5 may be entirely yellow, and the pronotum may have a small ventro-lateral blackish spot.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
